     65          /**
     66           *    @brief    This method Copies data from the RAM to the DataFlash as per the size and returns
     67           *              the response for write operation.
     68           *    @details  This method writes data from source (RAM) to destination (Data Flash) as per the size
     69           *              and returns the response for the write operation.
     70           *            Note -
     71           *                  1. Implemented in this API - Dataflash (EEPROM) byte must be in erased state before being programmed.
     72           *                  2. Controller supports byte by byte and 1 long write.
     73           *                  3. The software design supports for both even and odd size write.
     74           *
     75           *    @param    destination : Defines the address of the Data flash where data to be written
     76           *    @param    source      : Defines the address of RAM from where data to be written to flash
     77           *    @param    size        : Number of bytes to be written
     78           *    @return   enum DATAFLASH_RESPONSE_TYPE
     79           *      @retval DATAFLASH_RESPONSE_DONE(0)                 : If the write operation is complete.
     80           *      @retval DATAFLASH_RESPONSE_WRITE_ERROR(3)          : If the write operation is unsuccessful.
     81           *      @retval DATAFLASH_RESPONSE_ERROR_OUT_OF_RANGE(4)   : If the requested memory is out of range
     82           *      @retval DATAFLASH_RESPONSE_INVALID_SIZE(5)         : If the size is invalid i.e. odd size
     83           *
     84           */

